If these vector instructions are created after the vector GEP instruction, then we get the dominance violation.

The fix is to ensure that when vectorizing operands, we don't change the insertion point, or we restore it afterward.

However, the proper fix is to ensure that the operand vectorization happens at an insertion point that dominates the main instruction insertion point.

